<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="180">
Etymology Gr 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181664" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole chrysops Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysops">chrysops</taxonomicName>
, like gold, referring to the dark yellow color of the major.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="180">
Diagnosis A small, yellow species tentatively placed in the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142247" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Atta" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Atta diligens Smith" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diligens">diligens</taxonomicName>
group but with clear ties to some members of the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Atta" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">fallax</taxonomicName>
group, i.e., 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Atta" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aenescens">aenescens</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Atta" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bergi">bergi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Atta" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiceps">cordiceps</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Atta" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="midas">midas</taxonomicName>
, from which it is distinguished by the following set of traits.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="180">Major: head heart-shaped, but with occipital angles in full-face view tending toward subangulate; propodeal spine short, equilaterally triangular; pronotal profde in dorsal-oblique view slightly bilobous; pilosity long and dense; head lacking rugoreticulum, and carinulae limited to anterior half of head with frontal lobes mostly bare.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="180">Minor: occiput narrowed but lacking nuchal collar; in profile, mesonotum moderately convex.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="180">Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.94, HL 0.96, SL 0.74, EL 0.18, PW 0.52.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="180">Paratype minor: HW 0.46, HL 0.54, SL 0.66, EL 0.12, PW 0.34.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="180">Color Major: concolorous dark (&quot;golden&quot;) yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="180">Minor: clear medium yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="180">RANGE Known from the type locality and from a single series, nearly identical to the types, from Reserva Mbaracayii, Jejuimi, Dept. Canindeyu, Paraguay.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="180">BIOLOGY The Paraguay colony was in a nest in leaf litter in &quot;high forests&quot; (Alex Wild).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
